Key Delhi blast suspect arrested

Police in the Indian capital Delhi say they have arrested the suspected co-ordinator and financier of last month's deadly bomb blasts in the city. Delhi police chief KK Paul named the man as Tariq Ahmed Dar, and said police were hunting for four accomplices. He said Mr Dar, 33, was arrested in Indian-administered Kashmir and belonged to the outlawed Lashkar-e-Toiba militant group.

